Here I am repacking this incredible game.

Instead of describing the whole process here, I'm gonna ask you to read the old release readme
first (end of this document) and I'll only describe the differences between the old release and
this repack.

First, overburn is not necessary anymore. I was able to make extra space mono-ing ADPCM tracks I
missed before. Although there are only about five of them, and they're really hard to decode, I
had to work on them because in this game every single megabyte counts. I wrote my own tools for
that, and I'll share them in blog once I have time. Hum, I also made improvements in my DCZ
packer, and I'll share in my blog as well.

Some additional space could be obtained by re-linking redundant files.

Because of all space I made, I also could maintain most of multi-language. There are five
languages: English, Italian, Spanish, German and French. These languages are selected depending on
the one you set in BIOS. Texts of all languages are there. The opening scene is dubbed, but
because of space, Italian and German audio had to be ripped and re-linked to English ones. It
means that everything will work in every language, except that if you select German or Italian
you'll hear the opening in English. Not a big deal, right? Additionally, in the "Extra" folder of
the pack you can listen to the ripped audio.

Why did I chose German and Italian to rip? Well, Italian was chosen because it's the less spoken
language of the five. Then had to choose between German and French, but as U***oft is French, I
decided to maintain the original audio.

File order has changed for better, although I can't make miracles.

PAL users, when unpacking the image you'll have the option to patch the game so it will work in
60hz on your consoles.

That's all, enjoy another epic release from DCRES.


